android.permission.READ_PROFILE.description: Allows an application to read the user's personal profile data.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.FLASHLIGHT.description: Allows the application to control the flashlight.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.MOUNT_UNMOUNT_FILESYS.description: Allows the application to mount and unmount file systems for removable storage.

android.permission.REQUEST_INSTALL_PACKA.info: Allows an application to request installing packages.
android.permission.REQUEST_INSTALL_PACKA.description: Malicious applications can use this to try and trick users into installing additional malicious packages.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.WRITE_SETTINGS.description: Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

android.permission.READ_LOGS.description: Allows an application to read from the system's various log files. This allows it to discover general information about what you are doing with the phone, potentially including personal or private information.

playstore_details.description:
ViaBTC was founded in May 2016. It owns the world’s largest BCH mining pool and the fifth largest BTC mining pool, providing nearly one million users in 130+ countries/regions with professional, efficient and secure cryptocurrency mining services. It has accumulated a market value of billions of USD in total output. Currently, 16+ coins such as BTC, BCH, BSV, LTC, ETH, ZEC, DASH, XMR, etc. are available for mining. Based on its one-stop pool and wallet services, it aims to offer users with more stable mining services, more reliable tools, higher mining revenue and better user experience.
· Secure&Stable: 7*24 steady mining network
· Transparent: Real-time and detailed statistics of pools and miners
· Higher profit: Multiple settlement methods and mining forms 

Key Services: 

**Multi-cryptocurrency Pool**
Conduct mining of multiple coins and management of multiple accounts
Real-time hashrate/Daily profit details/Smart mining/Hashrate 

**Worker Management**
Learn the real-time status of mining farms and miners
Manage miners/Smart sorting/Batch move/Search miner

**Assets Management**
Digital assets' security guaranteed
Deposit/Withdraw/Auto withdraw/Auto convert

**Watcher Management**
Worry-free hosting, convenient maintenance
Watcher permissions/Favorites/External watchers

**Cloud Mining**
Lower costs for digital assets
Sufficient hashrate/Promised power/Free trading

Contact Us Website: https://www.viabtc.com/
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/viabtc
Twitter: https://twitter.com/viabtc_pool
Email: support@viabtc.com
